    "Continuing with data cleansing by handling unneeded values, autoencoders and probabilistic neural networks (PNN) for outlier detection, as well as recurrent neural networks (RNN) and convolutional neural networks (CNN) for data imputation or annotation.The authors of [32] provided an additional perspective on smart manufacturing while emphasizing the interconnection of data between actors and processes, and proposing a model for monitoring and interconnecting data by utilizing graphs for the creation of digital threads."
